            "title": "Returning values",
            "id": 80382,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>A function can return a value to the code that called it. This program returns a value to the code that called it to help perform its task.</p><webview version=\"2\" visible-if=\"always\" content=\"&lt;!doctype html&gt;&#xA;&lt;html&gt;&#xA; &lt;head&gt;&#xA;  &lt;style&gt;&#xA;   body {&#xA;    text-align: center;&#xA;    font-size: 16px;&#xA;    margin: 0 auto;&#xA;    background-color: #D5F5E3&#xA;   }&#xA;   &#xA;   button {&#xA;    background-color: #85C1E9;&#xA;    border: none;&#xA;    border-radius: 8px;&#xA;    color: white;&#xA;    text-align: center;&#xA;    text-decoration: none;&#xA;    display: inline-block;&#xA;    font-size: 14px;&#xA;    padding: 6px 12px;&#xA;    margin: 0 12px 0 0;&#xA;   }&#xA;   &#xA;   h2 {&#xA;    color: #7c795d;&#xA;    font-family: 'Trocchi', serif;&#xA;    font-size: 45px;&#xA;    font-weight: normal;&#xA;    line-height: 48px;&#xA;    margin: 0;&#xA;    text-align: centre&#xA;   }&#xA;   &#xA;   #playerList {&#xA;    text-align: left;&#xA;   }&#xA;  &lt;/style&gt;&#xA; &lt;/head&gt;&#xA; &lt;body id=&quot;main&quot;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;h2&gt;Pound Converter&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;  &lt;p&gt;Add value in pounds.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;  &lt;p&gt;&#xA;   &lt;label&gt;Pounds&lt;/label&gt;&#xA;   &lt;input id=&quot;inputPounds&quot; type=&quot;number&quot; placeholder=&quot;Pounds&quot;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/p&gt;&#xA;  &lt;button onClick=&quot;convert()&quot;&gt;convert&lt;/button&gt;&#xA;  &lt;p&gt;Kilograms: &lt;span id=&quot;outputKilograms&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;  &lt;script&gt;&#xA;   function convert() {&#xA;    const pounds = document.getElementById(&quot;inputPounds&quot;).value;&#xA;    document.getElementById(&quot;outputKilograms&quot;).innerHTML = pounds /&#xA;     2.2046;&#xA;   }&#xA;  &lt;/script&gt;&#xA; &lt;/body&gt;&#xA;&lt;/html&gt;\" /></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Return",
            "id": 80381,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Functions are written to perform tasks and sometimes, we may need the outcome of the tasks, this can be done via <code>return</code>.</p><p>To return something from a function we add the <code>return</code> keyword followed by the value to return, like here with <code>return label</code>.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"def\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"age_label\" class=\"title\" /><text value=\"(age)\" class=\"params\" /><text value=\":\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  label = \" /><text value=\"&quot;User age: &quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\" + age\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  \" /><text value=\"return\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" label\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"51\" endIndex=\"57\" /><option startIndex=\"58\" endIndex=\"63\" /></options></interaction></interactions></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>return</code>, followed by <code>label</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Return",
            "id": 80380,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>A function can return any type of value, like a string, integer, float, or boolean. We call this value the function's \"output\".</p><p>In the example below, we want the function to output the <code>result</code> of the <code>number</code> parameter multiplied by 10.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"def\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"times_ten\" class=\"title\" /><text value=\"(number)\" class=\"params\" /><text value=\":\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  result = number * \" /><text value=\"10\" class=\"number\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  \" /><text value=\"return\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" result\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"validatedInput\" isDefault=\"true\" startIndex=\"55\" endIndex=\"61\" /></interactions></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to type <code>result</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Return",
            "id": 80378,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>We can use the return value of a function like any value by calling the function. Here, we call <code>age_label(\"22\")</code> to use its value.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"def\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"age_label\" class=\"title\" /><text value=\"(age)\" class=\"params\" /><text value=\":\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  label = \" /><text value=\"&quot;User age: &quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\" + age\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  \" /><text value=\"return\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" label\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"print(age_label(\" /><text value=\"&quot;22&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\"))\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"71\" endIndex=\"86\" /><option correct=\"false\"><content><text value=\"age_label(age)\" /></content></option></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"User age: 22\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>age_label(\"22\")</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Storing it in a variable",
            "id": 80377,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>We can store the return value in a variable too. Here we store the return value in <code>result</code> and display it in the console.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"def\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"age_label\" class=\"title\" /><text value=\"(age)\" class=\"params\" /><text value=\":\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  label = \" /><text value=\"&quot;User age: &quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\" + age\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  \" /><text value=\"return\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" label\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"result = age_label(\" /><text value=\"&quot;29&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"print(result)\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"65\" endIndex=\"71\" /><option startIndex=\"74\" endIndex=\"89\" /><option startIndex=\"96\" endIndex=\"102\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"User age: 29\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>result</code>, followed by <code>age_label(\"29\")</code>, and finally <code>result</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "No return statement",
            "id": 80376,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>If we don't include a <code>return</code> statement, the function returns the value <code>None</code> instead.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"def\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"age_label\" class=\"title\" /><text value=\"(age)\" class=\"params\" /><text value=\":\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  label = \" /><text value=\"&quot;User age: &quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\" + age\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"result = age_label(\" /><text value=\"&quot;29&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"print(result)\" /></content><output><content><text value=\"None\" /></content></output></code></body></html>"
          },
